00:47:16,010 --> 00:47:17,271
As somebody that's usually blind

963
00:47:17,451 --> 00:47:18,892
to some of the things you described today,

964
00:47:19,693 --> 00:47:21,274
what's advice you could give somebody like me

965
00:47:21,314 --> 00:47:23,656
in the crowd to help somebody like that?

966
00:47:24,690 --> 00:47:24,891
Hmm.

967
00:47:25,431 --> 00:47:28,053
I feel like that is a good question.

968
00:47:28,193 --> 00:47:28,514
Thank you.

969
00:47:28,834 --> 00:47:30,756
So for anyone who didn't hear, for those

970
00:47:31,396 --> 00:47:35,159
for people who do not, who are somewhat blind to mental health

971
00:47:35,179 --> 00:47:37,541
issues, or I think this is probably even more broadly

972
00:47:37,581 --> 00:47:39,543
applicable to just issues that you may not see,

973
00:47:40,764 --> 00:47:45,388
what advice do I have to be understanding and comforting

974
00:47:45,468 --> 00:47:46,789
for those people?

975
00:47:48,150 --> 00:47:48,811
Yeah, I think that.

976
00:47:52,850 --> 00:47:57,533
from my perspective, really has to do with the environment that you're cultivating, right?

977
00:47:58,994 --> 00:48:03,036
And the things that you are asking, I mean, it depends on the relationship, right?

978
00:48:03,056 --> 00:48:07,978
Like an employer to employee relationship is slightly different than an employee to

979
00:48:08,038 --> 00:48:11,380
employee relationship, or I don't know, just people within the same industry.

980
00:48:12,500 --> 00:48:19,184
Listening for people who are willing to talk about it is an extremely important thing,

981
00:48:19,484 --> 00:48:21,825
and listening in a way that is not necessarily.

982
00:48:22,288 --> 00:48:24,508
like you trying to give a solution to someone else

983
00:48:24,769 --> 00:48:30,050
or you trying to, I don't know, help them in some way.

